	D. At December 31, 2015, the cost of investment securities for tax purposes was $4,652,971,000. Net unrealized appreciation of investment securities for tax purposes was $2,989,085,000, consisting of unrealized gains of $3,196,679,000 on securities that had risen in value since their purchase and $207,594,000 in unrealized losses on securities that had fallen in value since their purchase.










